â€œI donâ€™t give a fuck about what people think.â€
This Line sounds like bullshit to me.
Its so much overused and I think its just a very self centered and negative way to go about things.

I feel when we dont care about what people think or how it impacts everyone around us it makes us feel free and we do things that feel right to us and cut off from the outside noise and it certainly works but not always.

It makes the person less receptive to the opinions of everyone around them , people say positive and negative things and I feel to grow/learn its way better to just hear what others have to say.

Not giving a fuck seems pretty easy but its a little challenging to understand where people are coming from. It could be that the guy giving hate comments on a pic of urs is just fed up with his life and is giving out hate to get attention
Or
Maybe Hes giving hate because the pic was actually disturbing to him.

Either way, having empathy for other peopleâ€™s opinions is something i believe brings in perspective and helps us makes the best choice.

And sometimes positive reinforcement might make us feel good but it could also be that the person whos giving it doesnt want to hurt our feelings by telling the truth.

I could be wrong but I 100% give a fuck about what people say,I care deeply about the opinions of others and i try to understand where they are coming from and its a little challenging when its all negative but I feel its necessary.
Giving is the Secret ğŸ”¥ğŸ”¥ğŸ”¥

I thought i might share this one thing that I think is the reason why I have cultivated a little bit of success with youtube and all of this social media.

I met a few people today who told me that i am very talented and smart, speaking and making videos comes so naturally to me.

Trust me that is far from the truth, I dont think I am talented or smart, everything that you see in has been learned, Forget about speaking on camera or on stage, i couldnt speak to people in everyday conversations, i didnt know anything about making videos or technology or business or just basic life skills. And i also take a lot more time as compared to an average person to learn anything, but I dont mind it, i like the process. I have spent so much time learning basic things that come so naturally to most people its funny, and I will be honest i am still not very good at a lot of basic things. 
Learning is something that has stuck with me and although i am not the most consistent person, I have been very persistent with improving and learning things and I hope I can continue doing that while enjoying life haha.

I feel being Happy is not important, i would say its confusing. 
A lot of you guys ask me how do i stay happy all the time? I Donâ€™t! I dont even worry about staying happy.

If you look at the world around you, most things that are impactful, deep songs or powerful movies or even big ngoâ€™s or businesses were created when the person was going through a tough phase and could even be in the saddest of times and thats why they are so impactful.

I feel happiness is just an emotion just like being sad or being angry and they all are equally important but ofcourse we prefer being in the comfortable one.
Its like a state it comes and goes, and if you are not in control you will feel anxious and worried because you are not in the state you want to be in.

I feel its more important to be conscious and in control of your emotional state rather than just rely on happiness coming to you.
All the People who created amazing things in the darkest of their times just decided to take control of what they could do and not let their state decide what they do.

I think being happy is an outcome of doing the right things and To be able to create happiness is more important than being happy.

Its the same for money or pretty much anything, having money is not important but having the knowledge to create wealth is.
I am still in the process and I could be wrong but
I decided to share it, because it has helped me and worked for me. ğŸ”¥ğŸ”¥ğŸ”¥ I would say 
Dont chase happiness, chase the process of creating happiness for yourself.
Similarly dont chase money, chase the process of creating wealth.
